Reminders for Tonight's Game

1. Gates open at 6:00 pm
2. No tickets available to purchase at the gate.

post_text:
We have been watching and periodically checking the road situation throughout the day. It appears that getting kids home on buses will not be too difficult. We may need to take a few detours, but we can get the kids home safely.

The latest forecast is calling for more rain tonight. The possibility of more rain does have us concerned about what we may wake up to in the morning. At this time, we are still planning on school starting at normal time in the morning. We are planning on buses running in the morning but they MAY be running slower and arrive a little later than usual at the pickup points. Depending on the amount of rain we receive overnight, our morning start plans may have to be altered. If plans change, we will send information to you using ParentSquare.

Thank you for your understanding and cooperation.

Yesterday all Texas schools received a reminder from UIL about the things we are required to follow regarding the holding of UIL events - which at this time is Football and Volleyball games for Gustine ISD. Below you will find a link with the information shared with school districts.

We would like to point out that Gustine ISD could be "subject to sanctions" if we do not follow the guidelines. We ask that you please do your part and follow the guidelines when you attend any Gustine ISD athletic event - both home and away.

We would also remind you that when we are traveling to other schools, we must comply with how the home team is choosing to implement the guidelines.

post_text:
First week is successfully behind us!!

Thanks to all the parents that brought their kids back to school. Thank you for helping your kids be positive and optimistic even in the face of the COVID-19 concerns and fears.

Thanks to all the teachers and staff. There are so many stories from across Texas about teachers and staff members refusing to return to school. Every Gustine ISD teacher and staff member happily and willing returned to school this week. You made this week successful.

Thanks to all the Gustine ISD students. You have been amazing this week. You have done everything we asked you to do without fussing and grumbling. You have taken ownership in keeping each other safe and healthy.

If this week is any indication of how the year is going to go - then this is going to be one incredible school year!!!!

Thanks to all the Gustine ISD students. You have been amazing this week. You have done everything we asked you to do without fussing and grumbling. You have taken ownership in keeping each other safe and healthy.

If this week is any indication of how the year is going to go - then this is going to be one incredible school year!!!!

post_text: GREAT NEWS! We know that this is short notice but we are going to be able to have an in-person elementary open house for those students that will be attending school on-campus. On Thursday of this week from 6:00-6:30 we will be open for Pre-K, 1st, and 2nd grades to come and meet their teachers. From 6:30-7:00 we will be open for Kindergarten, 3rd, 4th, and 5th grades to come and meet their teachers. We will have to follow all Covid 19 protocols. All attendees will need to wear face masks or face shields. Everyone will also need to be screened as they enter. In addition we ask that the students attend with parents only and not whole families. This will help us keep the numbers down. Again this will only be available to students that will be attending school on campus.

UPDATE: Remember we are living in the "At This Time" world right now.

In previous communication we said that grades Pre-K through 5 would not be allowed to carry backpacks or other bags to and from school. Because we have continued to think through how we will be using technology off and on this year, we are changing that guideline and will allow students in grades Pre-K through 5 to carry backpacks or other bags to and from school. Since there will be times that they will be transporting technology devices to and from school, they will need a bag of some sort to carry that technology. Students in grades 6-12 were already being allowed to carry backpacks due to the removal of lockers. Stay tuned for more information coming soon.

post_text:
Parents - We need to ask for your help. We have been seeing and hearing that a bunch of our kids have been hanging out at The Pavilion. We know your kids are tired of being home. We also know that it is hard on you to have them home all the time. But, especially now that we have confirmed cases of COVID -19 in Gustine, hanging out at The Pavilion is not a safe thing for our kids to be doing - especially without wearing a mask. It is also not safe for them to go hang out at each other’s houses - especially if they are not all wearing masks.

If we want to start school any time soon, we have to find a way to slow the spread of COVID-19. We can’t guarantee that there will not be spread but we can slow it down and keep it to a manageable level. If we can keep it manageable, we can figure out how to have school.

Please help us keep the kids of Gustine safe! Thank you.

I know that many of you are wondering what is going to happen for Gustine ISD this school year. I wanted to assure you that we have been working on plans but we have not been in a hurry to release those plans. We are keeping a close eye on the situation in Comanche County and the counties surrounding us. There are 30 days from today before we hope to have students back on campus. We know that the COVID-19 situation is changing almost daily. So we feel like it is too early to 100% finalize our plans

However, with that said, this week we are planning on mailing out and posting information about the health and safety precautions we are planning on taking. We want to get your feedback regarding our thoughts and plans. Please be watching for this information later this week.

post_text:
Se encuentra disponible la solicitud de la Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios por Pandemia (P-EBT, por sus siglas en inglés). Debería haber recibido un correo electrónico o una carta de la escuela con más información sobre cómo solicitar estos beneficios de alimentos. La P-EBT es para los niños que recibieron beneficios de alimentos del Programa Asistencial de Nutrición Suplementaria (SNAP, por sus siglas en inglés) para marzo de 2020 y para los niños que están certificados para recibir comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido en Texas durante el año escolar 2019-20. Podría recibir hasta $285 por niño en una tarjeta de la P-EBT para comprar alimentos en las tiendas. Si su escuela no le envió información sobre la P-EBT, comuníquese con 833-613-6220. Visite hhs.texas.gov/PEBT para obtener más información.

GUSTINE ISD ENVIARÁ LA CARTA POR CORREO EL JUEVES 4 DE JUNIO DE 2020.

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Because Gustine ISD is a Community Eligibility Provision (CEP) District, all students that were enrolled in Gustine ISD at the end of the 2019-2020 school year will qualify for this program. However, families are responsible for completing all applications that can be accessed at the link above.

post_text:
Graduation Part 2

Please remember that we are to follow social distancing guidelines while attending the ceremony. Here is what that means:

1. We are to stay 6 feet apart - unless you live in the same house. When you are entering the field and during all other times, please maintain this distance.

2. Because of the deep cleaning/sanitizing guidelines that would have to be followed, we will not have buildings open for bathroom access.

3. The Ceremony will be pretty short. Part of following social distancing guidelines is limiting the time we are in large groups.

4. At the end of The Ceremony, we ask that you stay seated and wait for your family and friends to be dismissed. This will assist all guests in meeting the 6 foot social distancing.

5. Again, we are not requiring that you wear a mask, but we are strongly encouraging it.

We were notified last Thursday about this---

"The Dollar General Literacy Foundation recently awarded Gustine ISD a $2000 grant to support summer literacy. This local grant is part of more than $8.6 million in grants awarded to more than 950 schools, nonprofits and organizations across the communities Dollar General serves."

Gustine ISD applied for this grant before guidelines and restrictions were put in place for the Coronavirus. This means we are having to modify our original plans to stay in compliance with The Governor's Orders.

Be watching for more information to be posted soon!

The following information was just released by the Comanche County Judge’s Office :

COMANCHE COUNTY, TEXAS- Comanche County Judge Stephanie L. Davis and Local Public Health Authorities, Dr. Paul Livingston and Dr. Dwayne Miller, are reporting the sixth positive test result for COVID-19 in Comanche County, Texas. The resident had traveled outside of Comanche County and has been in quarantine since returning to Comanche County and being tested.

I know we are all getting tired of this “new normal”. But, we cannot let up on following all the health guidelines so we all stay safe and healthy. There are quite a few events taking place in Gustine over the next week including Graduation. PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE - be smart and follow precautions.

Hemos comenzado a divulgar información a las personas mayores y sus familias sobre la graduación. No tenemos todos los detalles listos para lanzar. Hemos recibido aprobación para partes de lo que planeamos hacer, pero todavía no tenemos aprobación para todo.

Lo que podemos decirle es que tenemos que limitar el número de personas que pueden asistir a la ceremonia. Tenemos que hacer esto para cumplir con las pautas de distanciamiento social y las órdenes del gobernador. Estamos tratando de hacer que todo funcione para transmitir la ceremonia en vivo para aquellos que no pueden asistir a la ceremonia.

Cuando tengamos todos los detalles resueltos, los publicaremos para la Comunidad. Gracias de antemano por su paciencia y comprensión. Sabemos que esto es difícil para las familias y deseamos no tener que celebrar la graduación de esta manera.

We have started releasing information to Seniors and their families regarding graduation. We do not have all of the details ready to release. We have received approval for parts of what we plan to do but we do not have approval for everything yet.

What we can tell you is that we are having to limit the number of people that can attend the ceremony. We have to do this to comply with Social Distancing Guidelines and the Governor’s Orders. We are trying to get everything worked out to live stream the ceremony for those that cannot attend the ceremony.

When we have all the details worked out, we will post them for the Community. Thank you in advance for your patience and understanding. We know this is hard on families and wish we didn't have to hold graduation this way.

2020 Gustine ISD Graduation Update:

The Texas Commissioner of Education, Mike Morath, holds twice a week conference calls regarding COVID-19 with all Texas School Superintendents. Here are the highlights of what we were directly told today in regards to graduation.

1. "In person graduations are not allowable. It will be about 3 weeks until we issue more information about this."
2. " We (Texas Education Agency) are working to find ways to hopefully allow in-person graduations in some form to be approved."
3. "We (Texas Education Agency) will have more information for you about graduations in about 3 weeks."

Bottom line - Gustine ISD cannot make any decisions at this time regarding how we will move forward with 2020 Graduation. We have to wait until we receive further guidance to make any possible plans public.

Just a thought-

Instead of focusing on what this Senior class is missing out on, what if we were to look at it this way - “The Class of 2020 is so special they get a one of a kind graduation experience”? Think about it - they are the only class in Gustine ISD history that will have this kind of graduation!! They will be celebrated in a unique, unforgettable way!!!

We are still waiting on State guidance regarding graduation. So, I have no idea what we will and will not be able to do. But I promise they will have a special graduation! It may not be “traditional” but it will be special - just like this group of 14 students!

Once a Tiger, Always a Tiger!!!
Go Gustine!

One of the many challenges that has come up with the way things are ending this school year is the completion of the Yearbook. Mrs. Marburger would like some help from Senior parents. We would like for the senior parents to put together pictures and/or words of wisdom they would like to share with their senior. Basically senior dedication pages. We would then print these are part of the yearbook. Mrs. Marburger needs this information by May 8th. You can email the information to her at smarburger@gustine.esc14.net. You can also bring the items by the school.

Please reach out to Mrs. Marburger for more information. Thank you for your help.

post_text: At noon today, Governor Greg Abbott announced that Texas schools will be closed for the remainder of the year. Gustine ISD will be switching our main mode of communication over to ParentSquare. You should be receiving an invite either on your cell phone and/or email address. Please accept the invite. There is an app you can download to your phone that will make access the program easier.

We are switching to ParentSquare because it allows us to do many more things. For example, it has a call out feature. So we will now be able to do mass call outs if needed. ParentSquare also has features that help us communicate with our Spanish speaking families much more efficiently.

We will continue to use the Gustine ISD Facebook page and the Gustine ISD web page.

Thank you.

So, I’m hearing that bears are starting to show up in Gustine!!!! I have heard that they are hiding in people’s windows and when you walk around town you can see them in the windows! I think our Gustine ISD students better go on a bear hunt!!!! Get out and enjoy the weather and see if you can find bears around town! Please remember to use your manners and be polite. Don’t knock on people’s doors and don’t tear up their yards!

Patti Blue, Gustine ISD, Superintendent

Please do not come play on the playground at school.

I know it would seem safe since it is outdoors. But, based on what we know about the virus it takes hours, possibly days, for the virus to die on playground surfaces. Another issue is that we do not need a group gathering at the playground. Remember we are practicing social distancing which means stay about 6 feet away from each other. So, a game of basketball isn't a good idea either right now. Sorry!

Thanks again for all the understanding you guys are showing and for all the work you are doing to help keep our community safe and healthy.

Just letting you know that we received the following information from UIL today:

We have previously communicated that all UIL activities are suspended until March 30th. Given information related to school closures available at this time, we are extending that time frame. UIL games and contests will resume no earlier than Monday, May 4th. Prior to that date, to allow students and schools to reenter competition, UIL will provide a reasonable acclimatization period for rehearsals and practices to occur, consistent with the advice of local, state and federal officials. We will reevaluate the beginning dates for practices and rehearsals as we receive more information about schools resuming.

post_text:
Posted by Patti Blue, Gustine ISD Superintendent

Many of you have already received phone calls from your students' teacher or from someone else with the school. One of the steps we are taking today is to evaluate the travel and health of our students. We are not trying to "get in anyone's business" - we are just trying to make preparations for the safe return of all students on Thursday.

We have also been inquiring about internet access. We are thinking through what we will need to do if we have to enter into a longer shut down in the future.

Another question we are asking is if your student needs breakfast and lunch during our shut down. We want to make sure our kiddos do not go hungry and to minimize as much as possible the financial strain families may feel.

We greatly appreciate your cooperation as we work through the process keeping everyone safe and healthy!

Remember: Frequently wash your hands with soap and water for 20 seconds and cover your coughs and sneezes!

From Patti Blue - Gustine ISD Superintendent

This will be the first of a series of posts regarding Covid-19 and how Gustine ISD will be addressing the situation. Please be looking for future posts. to ensure you have received complete information.

Gustine ISD will be closed to students, Monday, March 16th through Wednesday, March 18th. Staff will report at 8:30 am on Monday, March 16th. Tentatively students will report at normal time on Thursday, March 19th. We will constantly be evaluating the situation as new information becomes available. If information is received that makes us feel it is in the best interest of Gustine ISD students, staff, and community to delay the return of students past Thursday, we will announce that through Facebook postings and on the District’s website. If a posting does not come from me, Patti Beaty Blue, then do not consider it an official Facebook posting.

The past couple of years we have had community members make and donate breakfast burritos. This has made it really easy to eat as we drive. If you would be willing to help us by making breakfast burritos, would you please let me know. We will need to make plans to feed about 70 people.

Thank you.

Thank you.

One of the things that passed during this last Texas Legislative session was a requirement that every district have a School Safety and Security Committee. 2 of the members must be parents or guardians of students enrolled in the district. If you would be willing to serve on this committee and your are a parent or guardian of a Gustine ISD student, please comment here, email me (pblue@gustine.esc14.net), or call me 325.667.7303 ext 300.

There are 3 required meetings - once in Fall, once in Spring, and once in the Summer. The meetings will be held late in the afternoon - like 3:30.

Thank you in advance for volunteering.
